trans-unit.source: Provides information about a serializable object.
The SerializableObjectData structure contains data that can be used to deserialize a serializable object.
To get a SerializableObjectData, call the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.ISerializableObjectContract.GetSerializableObjectData%2A> method of an <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.ISerializableObjectContract>.
The only SerializableObjectData field that contains a value for every serializable object is the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.ObjectId> field.
Represents an array that contains the length of each of the dimensions of the serializable array that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.
DimensionLengths is `null` if <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.IsArray> is `false`.
To be added.
Represents an array that contains the lower bound of each of the dimensions of the serializable array that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.
DimensionLowerBounds is `null` if <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.IsArray> is `false`.
To be added.
Represents an array that contains the indexes of the parent array that contains the serializable object that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.
ElementIndexes is `null` if <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.IsArrayElement> is `false`.
To be added.
Indicates whether the <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes a serializable array.
IsArray is `true` if the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes an array; otherwise, IsArray is `false`.
If IsArray and <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.IsArrayElement> are both `true`, the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes a jagged array.
To be added.
Indicates whether the <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes an element in a serializable array.
IsArrayElement is `true` if the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes an element in an array; otherwise, IsArrayElement is `false`.
If IsArrayElement is `true`, then <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.ParentId> identifies the array, and <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.MemberName> is `null`.
If <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.IsArray> and IsArrayElement are both `true`, the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes a jagged array.
To be added.
Represents the member name of the serializable object that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.

MemberName is `null` if the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes an object that is not a member of another object (that is, <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData.ParentId> is `null`).
To be added.
Represents the ID of the serializable object that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.
To create an object ID, implementations of <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.ISerializableObjectContract> can use the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ObjectIDGenerator?displayProperty=fullName> class.
To be added.
Represents the ID of the parent of the serializable object that this <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData"></xref> describes.
ParentId is `null` if the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.SerializableObjectData> describes a serializable object that is not a member of another object.
To be added.
